{
    "componentChunkName": "component---src-templates-post-template-js",
    "path": "/burn-it-all-down",
    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It was a dark room, except for the west wall. It was illuminated by four panels, two red, a blue, and a green. There were buttons below each of the panels. When pressed, the panel (and adjacent panels) switched their colors: red became blue, blue to green, and green to red. We needed to turn each of these panels red in order to pass."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"style":"text-align: center; width: 100%"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"iframe","properties":{"width":500,"height":250,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/escape-room-windows"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This was one of the more interesting puzzles we encountered when doing a recent escape room. We ended up using a \"skip puzzle\" pass on this because it's hard to think when you have single-digit number of minutes remaining to escape and when there are 3 other people in the room also pressing the buttons while you are trying to think. However, this puzzle seemed like something that would be interesting to ponder, so when I got home I had chat GPT code it up. It did a perfect job. Went from idea to code to deployed app all in ~5 min. Could have done it myself in maybe 60 min."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"But it's not that difficult to solve once you think about it for a bit. What might be more interesting is generalizing the puzzle to a second dimension. Chat GPT struggled to code this by itself, but between the LLM and some old fashioned manual software engineering we now have a new version of the escape room game. This iteration also includes some nifty icons for the color-vision impaired."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"burn-it-all-down","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#burn-it-all-down","ariaLabel":"burn it all down permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Burn it all down"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Your goal, like before, is to turn everything to red fire, hence the title \"Burn it All Down\"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"style":"text-align: center; width: 100%"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=GqCA&width=3&height=3"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I found this to be pretty tricky, but after figuring out a few moves I think I can now solve any random 3x3 tile puzzles in less than a minute. It's easiest to develop these moves when starting from a homogenous grid. It's clear that if you get a homogenous tile grid (even if it's not red) victory is straight-forward. Clicking the middle will change the color of all the tiles until you get to the color you want (red)."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=VVVA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note that it might take either one (in the case of starting with green) or two clicks (for blue) to get a grid full of red. This maybe-one-click maybe-two-click behavior sometimes appears in the steps below and is noted by a (x2?) symbol."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, the strategy here is to make all the outside tiles the same color - any color - then finish up the middle tile last. Tiles on the outside can either be edges or corners. Here is how to solve both types."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"edge-tiles","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#edge-tiles","ariaLabel":"edge tiles permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Edge Tiles"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case, we'll change the problematic tile."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=VFVA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We click:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The bad tile twice"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"1st tile adjacent to the bad tile (in the case the one right above the bad tile)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"2nd tile adjacent to the bad tile (in the case the one right below the bad tile)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"(x2?)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Order is not important, as long as you click each of those tiles, you'll be okay."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Notice that this move also changes the center tile, but that's okay because we'll fix that at the end."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"corner-tiles","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#corner-tiles","ariaLabel":"corner tiles permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Corner Tiles"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this case we'll change everything except the problematic corner."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=gAAA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We click:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The tile catty-corner to the bad tile twice! (i.e. the tile furthest from the bad tile)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"1st tile adjacent to the catty-corner tile (in the case the one right above the catty-corner tile)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"2nd tile adjacent catty-corner tile (in the case the one to the left of the catty-corner tile)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"(x2?)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Again, it doesn't matter what order you choose but you'll see in this example that you'll have to do these steps two times.\r\nOnce to turn all the other squares blue and again to turn them green to match the original corner."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"radial-symmetry","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#radial-symmetry","ariaLabel":"radial symmetry permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Radial Symmetry"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, once you've used the moves above to ensure that all the edges and corners are set, we can handle the middle. Unless you've already won. There's a 1 in 3 change of automatic victory so your odds aren't too bad!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Lets assume you haven't won and instead you have a pretty wreath with green on the outside and a pesky red tile in the middle."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=qiqA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We need to turn this into a checkerboard before we can solve this by clicking all the edges. i.e."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"North tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"East tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"South tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"West tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"(x2?)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The first time you do these moves it will either turn the game into a checkerboard OR a cross. The second time you do these moves it will turn into whatever it didn't turn into the first time. We want the checkerboard."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{"width":200,"height":200,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=ZmZA&width=3&height=3","refreshable":"true"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"refreshable-iframe","properties":{},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To solve a checkerboard just click all the corners. Or if you prefer explicit compass directions:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NW tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NE tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SE tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SW tile"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"(x2?)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Remember you may need to do this twice."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Huzza! You win!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"impossible-puzzles","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#impossible-puzzles","ariaLabel":"impossible puzzles permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Impossible Puzzles"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After experimenting with a few different tile heights and widths it became pretty clear that not all puzzles are solvable. The most obvious example is a 1x2 or 2x1 grid in which each square starts as a different color, but there are plenty of others:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"style":"text-align: center; width: 100%"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"iframe","properties":{"width":250,"height":250,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=gA&width=1&height=2"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"iframe","properties":{"width":250,"height":250,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=ZoY&width=2&height=4"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"iframe","properties":{"width":250,"height":250,"style":"border: solid 1px grey; border-radius: 6px;","src":"https://thbrown.github.io/burn-it-all-down/?colors=VYA&width=1&height=5"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I wrote a dynamic programming algorithm to determine solvability of individual puzzles (seems like a good interview question), it doesn't work well on large grids and it uses bloom filters so it's results are probabilistic. Here is a table showing my estimated solvability of different tile puzzles based in their heights and widths."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"estimated-puzzle-solvability","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#estimated-puzzle-solvability","ariaLabel":"estimated puzzle solvability permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Estimated Puzzle Solvability"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"YES only if all variations are solvable."}]},{"type"